EmailTemplate.name: HT/DR 2016 - Final Email
EmailTemplate.subject: Final details about your trip!
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Build Volunteers,
Can you believe that in just a week and a half and you will be in the Dominican Republic and Haiti?! I am so excited for each of you to experience this trip.
Before you take off, we have some important information and reminders. There is a lot of important information below. Please take the time to read it thoroughly!
Please note that if you have any questions, please email me before the end of this week so that I can get back to you promptly. I am getting married next Saturday, July 16, and will be taking next week off of work. However, I will be checking my emails at night before I go to bed. For emergency inquiries, you are able to call the office at 905-777-1662 and anyone can assist you. If it's not urgent, you can wait for me to send you an email back. But please, try to connect with me over the next couple of days!
1. ARRIVAL and ACCOMMODATIONS
When you arrive into Puerto Plata, please be prepared with $10 USD to purchase your tourist card (unless you fly with WestJet, as they cover that for you). On you tourist cards you can write, "Sosua by the Sea" for your address within the Dominican.
Our staff will be waiting for you as you come out of the airport. They will be wearing a Live Different t-shirt or holding a Live Different Build sign. They will bring you to the hotel to settle in.
In Cap Haitian we will be staying at the Royal Residency Guest House. This safe and clean hotel will feel more like a friendly home than a hotel. It has a wonderful view of the city and amazing food.
This guest house does not offer locked safes in your rooms. Please use caution when considering packing anything of value to you (jewelry, computers, cell phones, etc). You may want to bring a little lock for your luggage.
While in the Dominican Republic, you will be staying at a resort called Sosua by the Sea. This resort is approximately 15 minutes from the Puerto Plata airport and is home to all our teams that travel with us to the Dominican.
2. PASSPORTS
Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be given to staff, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling.
3. PACKING LIST
Please read through the packing list thoroughly to ensure that you have everything you need for your trip. Often, our volunteers pack the night before and realize that they need to purchase some items. It is easier to do this a week early!
4. EMERGENCY CONTACTS
If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency, these are the numbers to call:
Live Different Build Office:1-866-432-4464 (toll free) Brett (DR): 1 829 675 3684 Cole (DR): 1 829 305 8198 Cole (Haiti): 011 509 389 23909
Sosua by the Sea: 809-571-3222 Royal Residency (Cap Haitien): 509-2553-1458
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email at joy@livedifferent.com.
5. PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS
There is wi-fi access at the Royal Residency but the internet connection is fairly poor. Please come prepared to be off grid while in Haiti. Wireless is available at our hotel in the Dominican Republic for either $2 an hour or $5 a day (all in USD).
6. SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY
- It is best to bring cash in USD as both countries will accept it. - Please consider the following when deciding how much spending money to bring:
Your meals while traveling to and from your home to Puerto Plata, as well as some snacks during our road trip to Haiti Any personal spending (for things like souvenirs or snacks) $30 USD Resort staff tip - suggested amount $20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team.
7. YOUR LIVE DIFFERENT STAFF
Brett, Mark, Cole and Katie will be your trip hosts. They're looking forward to meeting you all! (And seeing some familiar faces!)
Thank you for taking the time to read through all of that very important information. If you have any questions, please feel free to send me an email or I can always give you a call.
Have a great trip!
Joy Yu Program Administrator
